    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 7 Engine Service Manual - Cylinder Head and Valve Train - Installation
        - Fuel Injector and Rail Assemblies
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s10.4.10" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="6">
        <title>Fuel Injector and Rail Assemblies</title>
        <figure id="f3450010085" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM08/M08151.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Fuel injector seal and combustion gasket (typical)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel injector seal</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Combustion gasket</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para id="s10.4.10.ref1">To prevent engine damage, install new fuel injector seal and combustion gasket
                    if a fuel injector is removed.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Make sure to install new combustion gasket oriented as noted during removal.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new combustion gasket onto injector tip.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To seat gasket, push on gasket with a deep socket.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and discard old fuel injector seal.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new fuel injector seal. Lubricate fuel injector seal with clean engine oil.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450010086" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM08/M08117.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Fuel injector assembly (typical)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel injector assembly (4)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Injector clamp bolt (4)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Injector hold down clamp (4)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, do not use power tools.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install fuel injector assembly by lowering fuel injector and injector hold down clamp
                assembly as one unit into injector bore.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Injectors must be fully seated, but moveable, for installation of fuel rail to injector tube
                    assemblies.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Hand start clamp bolts. Pre-tighten injector clamp bolts to 2 N&#183;m (18 lbf&#183;in).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply a water based rubber lubricant, such as
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_237.xml" xrefid="s10.t3">P-80&#174; Rubber Lubricant or equivalent</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s10.t3"/>, to outer and inner diameters of fuel supply line seal.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450010087" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM08/M08168.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Fuel supply line seal installation (typical)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel supply line seal</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Valve cover base</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new fuel supply line seal by pressing it with a proper size socket toward the
                outside of the valve cover base.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450010088" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM08/M08115.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Rail assembly (typical)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Rail assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 x 30 bolt (2)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Rail assembly must be fully seated but moveable for installation of fuel rail to injector tube
                    assemblies.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install rail assembly and two M8 x 30 bolts. Hand tighten bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove all
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_237.xml" xrefid="s10.t3">Fuel System Caps ZTSE4710</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s10.t3"/>
                from fuel rail and fuel injector assemblies.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450010089" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM08/M08114.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Fuel rail to injector tube assemblies (typical)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel rail to injector tube assembly (4)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Tube nut (8)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent personal injury or death, whenever any fuel line (tubing) in the high-pressure fuel
                    system is removed, it must be replaced with new.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position four new fuel rail to injector tube assemblies between fuel injector assemblies and
                rail assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450010090" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM08/M08172.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Fuel rail to injector tube assemblies tightening sequence (typical)</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Hold fuel rail to injector tube assemblies while hand tightening nuts to assure proper assembly of
                    joints.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>When using a crowfoot extension make sure to adjust the torque settings as necessary to compensate
                    for any length added to the torque wrench. See
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_344.xml" xrefid="s19.1.ref1">Appendix B - Torques</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s19.1.ref1"/>.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Fully hand start and seat nuts onto mating connections of all fuel tubes, then pre-tighten
                with a crowfoot torque wrench following sequence shown in
                <xref refid="f3450010090"/>
                to 2 N&#183;m (18 lbf&#183;in).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten injector clamp bolts to 38 N&#183;m (28 lbf&#183;ft).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten two M8 x 30 rail assembly bolts to 31 N&#183;m (23 lbf&#183;ft).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using a crowfoot torque wrench and a second wrench to hold the fuel injector fittings,
                continue to tighten fuel rail to injector tube assembly nuts following sequence shown in
                <xref refid="f3450010090"/>. Tighten four nuts on the fuel injector assemblies first, then four nuts on
                the rail assembly as follows:
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Tighten nuts to 16 N&#183;m (142 lbf&#183;in).</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Tighten nuts an additional 60&#176;.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_74.xml" xrefid="s03.5.3.ref1">Under Valve Cover (UVC) harness</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s03.5.3.ref1"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
